Task.Name: 2005 Nursing Schedule
Task.Notes:
The purpose of this template is to give you the ability to track the schedule of nursing assignments against scheduled time off. This template has been created using Microsoft Project so that dates, resources, work disposition and other assignment information can be entered to manage vacation requests, sick days and general availability. To accomplish this, the template has been separated into two key areas: Vacation / PTO (Paid Time Off) Schedule and Nurse Work Schedule.
Vacation / PTO Schedule
The purpose of this section is to capture the schedule for when a member of the nursing staff will be unavailable to work due to scheduled vacation, sick time, or any other paid time off. This section has been categorized based each month in the year. The manager of this schedule must enter the following information: Task Name. Enter the name of the resource and the type and status for the time off that has been requested (ex. Ryan Ihrig - Vacation: Approved). Duration. Enter the number of days the employee has requested within the month. Start/Finish. Enter the Start Date the employee intends to begin the scheduled time off (the Finish Date will automatically populate based on the previously entered Duration). Resource Names. Select the name of the resource (populated from the Resource Sheet). Assignment ID. Enter the unique number used to identify the assignment the employee is assigned to during the scheduled time off (enter N/A if the employee is not assigned at the time). Work Disposition. Select the type of scheduled time off the employee has requested.
Nurse Work Schedule
The purpose of this section is to capture the schedule information for when a member of the nursing staff is unavailable due to an assignment. The manager of the schedule must enter the following information: Task Name. Enter the name and a brief description for the assignment that the nursing resource(s) are assigned. Duration. Enter the number of days the employee will be assigned (for long term assignments enter the Start and Finish Dates and the Duration will automatically calculate). Start/Finish. Enter the Start and Finish Dates for the time the employee will be assigned. Resource Names. Select the name of the resource (populated from the Resource Sheet). Assignment ID. Enter the unique number used to identify the assignment. Work Disposition. Select the appropriate work shift the employee will perform work (1st, 2nd or 3rd).
The following views are available to see variations of the data entered:
Calendar. This view is used to view information in a calendar mode. Select a resource name and date range to view activities for the specified period of time or select cancel to view all activities. Gantt Chart (default view). This view is used to enter and manage employee assignment and time off information. Tracking Gantt. This view is used to graphically depict employee assignment and time off information. Resource Sheet. This view is used to capture all nursing resource information. All nursing resources should be entered on the Resource Sheet. Resource Usage. This view is used to graphically depict the usage of all employees over a given period of time.
Custom filters and groups have been created to assist in the manipulation of project data (for assistance with Groups and Filters, select help or type a question in the space provided).
Filters Employee Listing (1st Shift) Employee Listing (2nd Shift) Employee Listing (3rd Shift) Employee Listing (Unavailable/Pending TO Approval)
Groups Assignment ID Grouping Work Disposition Grouping
